# ORIG TITLE    Greek banks to be sold . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Two of Greece’s banks are set to be sold under the country’s plans to revive the finance sector. Smaller lenders Hellenic Postbank and Proton currently owned by The Hellenic Financial stability fund have been split into good and bad parts. The country’s four biggest banks are being recapitalised. Institutions deemed non-viable are being wound down . The whole recapitalisation process is expected to be wrapped up by June the 14th. 
